{
  "text": "To generate a CSI we need: (1) a color image in RGB 24-bit true color format and (2) a small set of arbitrarily located pixels forming a sample of the color desired to be segmented. From this sample of pixels we calculate the statistical indicators according to our HSI modified color model [CITATION_1] . This information is necessary to adapt the color similarity function in order to obtain good results. To obtain the CSI we calculate for every pixel ( ) j i, in the image the following color similarity function S : \u03c3 is the Intensity standard deviation of the sample. In Eq. (1) the color information is integrated giving high importance to perceptual small changes in hue, as well as giving wide or narrow tolerance to the intensity and saturation values depending on the initial sample, which is representative to the desired color to be segmented.",
